#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:4
msgid "Installing PostgreSQL Database Server"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:6
msgid ""
"Install and set up the database for use by the Mattermost server. You can"
" install either PostgreSQL or MySQL."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:8
msgid "Assume that the IP address of this server is 10.10.10.1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:10
msgid "**To install PostgreSQL on Ubuntu Server 16.04:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:12
msgid ""
"Log in to the server that will host the database and issue the following "
"command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:14
msgid "``sudo apt-get install postgresql postgresql-contrib``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:16
msgid ""
"When the installation is complete, the PostgreSQL server is running, and "
"a Linux user account called *postgres* has been created."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:18
msgid "Log in to the *postgres* account."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:20
msgid "``sudo --login --user postgres``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:22
msgid "Start the PostgreSQL interactive terminal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:24
msgid "``psql``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:26
msgid "Create the Mattermost database."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:28
msgid "``postgres=# CREATE DATABASE mattermost;``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:30
msgid "Create the Mattermost user 'mmuser'."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:32
msgid "``postgres=# CREATE USER mmuser WITH PASSWORD 'mmuser-password';``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:35
msgid "Use a password that is more secure than 'mmuser-password'."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:37
msgid "Grant the user access to the Mattermost database."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:39
msgid "``postgres=# GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE mattermost to mmuser;``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:41
msgid "Exit the PostgreSQL interactive terminal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:43
msgid "``postgres=# \\q``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:45
msgid "Log out of the *postgres* account."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:47
msgid "``exit``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:49
msgid ""
"(Optional) If you use a different server for your database and the "
"Mattermost app server, you may allow PostgreSQL to listen on all assigned"
" IP Addresses. To do so, open "
"``/etc/postgresql/9.5/main/postgresql.conf`` as root in a text editor. As"
" a best practice, ensure that only the Mattermost server is able to "
"connect to the PostgreSQL port using a firewall."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:51
#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:69
msgid "Find the following line:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:53
msgid "``#listen_addresses = 'localhost'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:55
msgid "Uncomment the line and change ``localhost`` to ``*``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:57
msgid "``listen_addresses = '*'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:59
msgid "Restart PostgreSQL for the change to take effect:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:61
msgid "``sudo systemctl restart postgresql``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:63
msgid ""
"Modify the file ``pg_hba.conf`` to allow the Mattermost server to "
"communicate with the database."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:65
msgid "**If the Mattermost server and the database are on the same machine**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:67
#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:79
msgid "Open ``/etc/postgresql/9.5/main/pg_hba.conf`` as root in a text editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:71
msgid "``local   all             all                        peer``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:73
msgid "Change ``peer`` to ``trust``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:75
msgid "``local   all             all                        trust``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:77
msgid "**If the Mattermost server and the database are on different machines**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:81
msgid ""
"Add the following line to the end of the file, where *{mattermost-server-"
"IP}* is the IP address of the machine that contains the Mattermost "
"server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:83
msgid "``host all all {mattermost-server-IP}/32 md5``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:85
msgid "Reload PostgreSQL:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:87
msgid "``sudo systemctl reload postgresql``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:89
msgid "Verify that you can connect with the user *mmuser*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:91
msgid ""
"If the Mattermost server and the database are on the same machine, use "
"the following command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:93
msgid "``psql --dbname=mattermost --username=mmuser --password``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:95
msgid ""
"If the Mattermost server is on a different machine, log into that machine"
" and use the following command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:97
msgid ""
"``psql --host={postgres-server-IP} --dbname=mattermost --username=mmuser "
"--password``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:100
msgid ""
"You might have to install the PostgreSQL client software to use the "
"command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:102
msgid ""
"The PostgreSQL interactive terminal starts. To exit the PostgreSQL "
"interactive terminal, type ``\\q`` and press **Enter**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-ubuntu-1604-postgresql.rst:104
msgid ""
"With the database installed and the initial setup complete, you can now "
"install the Mattermost server."
msgstr ""

